        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Shutter finish families</h3><p>Laminate-led, matte, glossy, acrylic-style, and wood-tone directions each change the maintenance profile and the visual character of the kitchen.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Countertop and backsplash pairing</h3><p>Cooking intensity, stain tolerance, and visual contrast matter here. A premium finish looks best when it is chosen with real use patterns in mind.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Hardware and movement quality</h3><p>Drawer action, hinges, tall pull-outs, corner accessories, and under-sink fittings shape the everyday experience far more than the front view alone.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Appliance integration</h3><p>Microwave niches, ovens, chimneys, dishwashers, and water units need proper allowances early so the finished kitchen looks calm and intentional.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Lighting and utility support</h3><p>Task lighting, electrical planning, and service access should be aligned with the layout so the kitchen feels considered after installation, not adjusted around it.</p></article>
