        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Measure the room honestly</h3><p>Wall lengths, openings, service points, and movement paths matter more than the inspiration image. They decide what can actually fit.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>List cooking and storage habits</h3><p>Heavy cooking, appliance use, pantry demand, and drawer expectations all shape how the kitchen should be organized.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Choose the finish tier early</h3><p>Material preference, hardware expectations, and countertop direction should be discussed before the design becomes too abstract.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Decide how soon the project starts</h3><p>Timeline, site readiness, and whether the home is being renovated or freshly set up all affect how the estimate should be framed.</p></article>
